<div id="review_436185600" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/436185600" />
    <a title="Diane Barnes" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7262060-diane-barnes"><img alt="Diane Barnes" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1329773692p2/7262060.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/436185600?book_show_action=true">Oct 17, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Diane Barnes" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Diane Barnes" href="/user/show/7262060-diane-barnes">Diane Barnes</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9781877853500" href="/book/show/1689935.The_Black_Flower">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7262060-diane-barnes?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer436185600" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11857490686792392230">This book took me a while to read, but was worth every second spent with it. I read slowly to digest the beauty of the language and the imagery, and considering that most of the novel is about death and dying and the futility of war, that speaks volumes about the talent of the author. The battle of Franklin, Tennessee and it&apos;s aftermath is depicted in such detail, and so poignantly, that it must be read slowly simply to digest it emotionally. This is the best Civil War novel I have ever read.</span>
  <span id="freeText11857490686792392230" style="display:none">This book took me a while to read, but was worth every second spent with it. I read slowly to digest the beauty of the language and the imagery, and considering that most of the novel is about death and dying and the futility of war, that speaks volumes about the talent of the author. The battle of Franklin, Tennessee and it's aftermath is depicted in such detail, and so poignantly, that it must be read slowly simply to digest it emotionally. This is the best Civil War novel I have ever read.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11857490686792392230" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review436185600">
