  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/840785287" />
    <a title="Bethany" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/22500308-bethany"><img alt="Bethany" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1446662239p2/22500308.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/840785287?book_show_action=true">Mar 14, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bethany" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bethany" href="/user/show/22500308-bethany">Bethany</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/22500308-bethany?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/22500308-bethany?shelf=civil-war">civil-war</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer840785287" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16187180765901920281">I had to read this book in a hurry before it was due back at the library, but that proved to be no trouble at all. The writing is gorgeous and the characters vivid. It&apos;s also refreshing to read a novel focusing on the war&apos;s Western theatre, in this case the Army of Tennessee and the Battle of Franklin. This is a must-read for Civil War buffs and I&apos;m anxious to read the author&apos;s other novels.</span>
  <span id="freeText16187180765901920281" style="display:none">I had to read this book in a hurry before it was due back at the library, but that proved to be no trouble at all. The writing is gorgeous and the characters vivid. It's also refreshing to read a novel focusing on the war's Western theatre, in this case the Army of Tennessee and the Battle of Franklin. This is a must-read for Civil War buffs and I'm anxious to read the author's other novels.</span>
