<div id="review_2308742360" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2308742360" />
    <a title="Alana Cash" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/31360589-alana-cash"><img alt="Alana Cash" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1405560402p2/31360589.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2308742360?book_show_action=true">Feb 25, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Alana Cash" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Alana Cash" href="/user/show/31360589-alana-cash">Alana Cash</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2308742360" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1118330104036929176">I&apos;m not sure I can do this book justice in a review. If I could give 10 stars, I would. This is a tragic, compelling, intense story from beginning to end. There&apos;s no romance about the Civil War, it&apos;s madness and pathos and uselessness. The men are hungry, ragged, emaciated, and dangerous, and yet so very human. Howard Bahr has an amazing ability to capture people and places in such a way that I feel that I&apos;m there and that the people are real. I&apos;m convinced these people lived. <br/><br/>Bahr&apos;s unique styl</span>
  <span id="freeText1118330104036929176" style="display:none">I'm not sure I can do this book justice in a review. If I could give 10 stars, I would. This is a tragic, compelling, intense story from beginning to end. There's no romance about the Civil War, it's madness and pathos and uselessness. The men are hungry, ragged, emaciated, and dangerous, and yet so very human. Howard Bahr has an amazing ability to capture people and places in such a way that I feel that I'm there and that the people are real. I'm convinced these people lived. <br /><br />Bahr's unique style weaves around one main character who interacts with the others. He gives a little storyline to each character as he introduces them - keeping them unforgettable. <br /><br />I cannot recommend this book enough!</span>
  <a data-text-id="1118330104036929176" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
